OL,7,F"In what can only be described as an
OL,8,Fact of wanton vandalism, the CCTV
OL,9,Fshows the two of you forcibly remove
OL,10,Fthe front facade of the Paddington
OL,11,Fstatue and carry him through the town
OL,12,Fto a taxi which took you and the
OL,13,Fstatute back to your base at RAF
OL,14,FOdiham.
OL,16,F"You were both under the influence of
OL,17,Falcohol. Paddington Bear was then
OL,18,Flocated in William Lawrence's vehicle.
OL,20,F"Paddington Bear is a beloved cultural
OL,21,Ficon with children and adults alike.
